<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="376" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1158,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1266,1291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Ocular pigment absent; dorsal shield without colour pattern; integument of dorsal shield with eight very lightly developed areas of radiating lines on inner surface; Cx-IV posterior to IV-L insertion without a longitudinal ridge; genital field with 
<number box="[562,632,1338,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" value="72.5" valueMax="75.0" valueMin="70.0">70–75</number>
pairs of acetabula on well-defined genital plates; III/IV-L- 
<number box="[1288,1301,1338,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[1310,1322,1338,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="376" value="5.0">5</number>
each with one short swimming seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
